Introduction

Dongwoo is a South Korean rapper, singer, and actor under INFINITE Company. He is a member of the boy group INFINITE and its now defunct sub-unit, INFINITE H. As a soloist, he promotes under his full name, Jang Dongwoo, and made his solo debut on March 4, 2019, with his first mini album, Bye.

He debuted as a member of INFINITE on June 9, 2010, with the release of their mini album First Invasion.

On March 31, 2021, Woollim Entertainment announced that Dongwoo, along with fellow member Sungyeol, had departed from the agency following the expiration of their contracts. Later that year, on October 1, he signed a short lived contract with Big Boss Entertainment. In September, he signed with Hi-Hat Entertainment but eventually transitioned to INFINITE Company, an agency founded by his fellow member Kim Sungkyu.
